	The encryption used by Apple's iMessage service is hindering federal drug enforcement agency investigations, says <a href=\"http://news.cnet.com/8301-13578_3-57577887-38/apples-imessage-encryption-trips-up-feds-surveillance/\">a report in CNET</a>. CNET obtained an internal Drug Enforcement Administration document that details the problem faced by agents who are tracking suspects using non-traditional communication methods.</p><p>
	According to the document, the end-to-end encryption used by iMessage makes it \"impossible to intercept iMessages between two Apple devices,\" even when there is a court order authorizing the electronic wiretap. This problem was discovered when agents noticed that messages sent from one iPhone to another iPhone via <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/tag/iMessage/\">iMessage</a> were not being captured during a surveillance.</p><p>
	The inability to adequately conduct surveillance is a growing problem for law enforcement. <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Mueller\">FBI director Robert Mueller</a> recently told Congress that \"there is a growing and dangerous gap between law enforcement's legal authority to conduct electronic surveillance, and its actual ability to conduct such surveillance.\" He asked Congress \"to ensure that the laws by which we operate and which provide protection to individual privacy rights keep pace with new threats and new technology.\"</p><p style=\"padding:5px;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/04/apples-imessage-encryption-thwarts-government-investigations/\">Apple's iMessage encryption thwarts government investigations</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Thu, 04 Apr 2013 11:30:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear:both;\"></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=http://news.cnet.com/8301-13578_3-57577887-38/apples-imessage-encryption-trips-up-feds-surveillance/>Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/04/apples-imessage-encryption-thwarts-government-investigations/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/forward/20530122/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/04/apples-imessage-encryption-thwarts-government-investigations/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments</a>") (category nil "Apple") (category nil "drug enforcement administration") (category nil "DrugEnforcementAdministration") (category nil "iCloud") (category nil "iMessage") (category nil "messaging") (category nil "surveillance") (dc:creator nil "Kelly Hodgkins") (pubDate nil "Thu, 04 Apr 2013 11:30:00 EST"))) ("New and notable apps for iOS and OS X - April 4 edition" "<p style=\"text-align:center;padding:0;margin:0 0 10px 0\"><img alt=\" \" border=\"0\" height=\"250\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com//media/2013/04/appstoreicon1813.jpg\" width=\"456\" /></p><p>
It has been busy in the App Store with a handful of new apps landing on iOS and OS X. Take a few minutes and check out our list of standout apps from the past week!</p><h3>
iOS Apps</h3><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/curved-text-that-curves/id584748197?mt=8\">Curved - Text that Curves</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Photography &amp; Video, Now free, down from $1.99]</strong> Curved helps you to add beautiful curved texts on your photo.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/annihilate/id604402549?mt=8\">Annihilate</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $0.99]</strong> An abstract dual-stick shooter with enough challenge to keep you coming back for more.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/final-fantasy-v/id609577016?mt=8\">FINAL FANTASY V</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $15.99]</strong> Twenty years after the original Final Fantasy V released in Japan, the classic RPG has found its way to mobile devices.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/tiny-troopers-2-special-ops/id594774843?mt=8\">Tiny Troopers 2: Special Ops</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $0.99]</strong> Decked out in new uniforms and sporting the latest in military hardware, the troopers are just itching to get back into the fight.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/quantum-legacy-hd-turbo/id593628504?mt=8\">Quantum Legacy HD Turbo</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $0.99]</strong> Team up with Colonel Seth Blair as you pilot one of four unique spaceships during your three-plus-hour journey through 20 action-packed Turbo missions.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/magicka/id588720940?mt=8\">Magicka</a> [iPad, Category: Games, $1.99]</strong> Magicka - Wizards of the Square Tablet: Now you can accidentally set your friends on fire from anywhere.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/nimble-quest/id583638819?mt=8\">Nimble Quest</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, Free]</strong> Lead a conga line of heroes to glory against hordes of enemies across an endless number of stages.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/ms.-splosion-man/id589642458?mt=8\">Ms. Splosion Man</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $2.99]</strong> At the Big Science after-party celebrating the capture of Splosion Man, a spill of champagne shorts out the safety protocols on the splosionatrix and from it emerges Ms. Splosion Man.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/gardenscapes-mansion-makeover/id585195879?mt=8\">Gardenscapes: Mansion Makeover HD</a> [iPad, Category: Games, Free]</strong> Having restored the garden to its beauty and grandeur, it's high time to have some guests over to show off! Thankfully, the mansion has a spacious hall for everyone to gather.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/frontline-commando-d-day/id567198973?mt=8\">Frontline Commando: D-Day</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, Free]</strong> Lead the charge on D-Day as the tip of the spear in the largest Allied invasion of WW2.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/little-inferno-pocket-edition/id604376012?mt=8\">Little Inferno Pocket Edition</a> [iPhone, Category: Games, $2.99]</strong> An adventure that takes place almost entirely in front of a fireplace -- about looking up up up out of the chimney, and the cold world just on the other side of the wall. From the designers of World of Goo and Henry Hatsworth in the Puzzling Adventure.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/shopster-geo-learning-groceries/id613223118?mt=8\">Shopster - The geo-learning groceries list</a> [iPhone, Category: Productivity, $0.99]</strong> Shopster is a new kind of groceries list app that learns what youpurchase and where, so it can remind you later on.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/disney-storytime/id597251953?mt=8\">Disney Storytime</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Business, $1.99]</strong> The largest collection of Disney stories in one app: 20 total stories available. Get three beautiful Disney stories with your app purchase, Toy Story: Starry Night, Tangled: Rapunzel's Story and Monsters, Inc.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/radar-cast-pro-noaa-hi-def/id601606659?mt=8\">Radar Cast Pro - NOAA Hi-Def FutureCast with Lightning Strikes</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Weather, $3.99]</strong> Amazing hi-definition, animated, real-time futurecast radar images with snowfall and lightning strikes on a fluid responsive map that loads faster than any other app in the App Store.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/duke-nukem-2/id619201240?mt=8\">Duke Nukem 2</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $1.99]</strong> Duke blasts his way through your screen with enough firepower to wake your neighbors.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/badland/id535176909?mt=8\">BADLAND</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $3.99]</strong> BADLAND is an award-winning atmospheric sidescrolling action adventure platformer located in a gorgeous forest full of various inhabitants, trees and flowers.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/the-other-brothers/id618605145?mt=8\">The Other Brothers</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $0.99]</strong> The Other Brothers is a platformer that will have you running, jumping, collecting and racing against the clock in a modern take on that time-tested genre.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/slayin/id548580856?mt=8\">Slayin</a> [iOS Universal, Category: Games, $0.99]</strong> Slay as many monsters as possible, while leveling up and getting more powerful equipment and spells along the way.</p><h3>
OS X Apps</h3><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/timebar/id617829225?mt=12\">Timebar</a> [OS X, Category: Productivity, $2.99]</strong> Timebar stays out of your way while making sure you don't lose track of time.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/ulysses-iii/id623795237?mt=12\">Ulysses III</a> [OS X, Category: Productivity, $19.99]</strong> Ulysses III is a brand-new writers' environment from the Soulmen -- the fine folks that brought you Daedalus Touch for iPad. It's built around a revolutionary engine, dubbed \"plain text enhanced\", which combines the very best parts of minimal markup (i.e. Markdown, Textile) with the power, beauty and simplicity of OS X.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/nimble-quest/id598685044?mt=12\">Nimble Quest</a> [OS X, Category: Games, Free]</strong> Lead a conga line of heroes to glory against hordes of enemies across an endless number of stages.</p><p><strong><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/ifax-send-receive-faxes/id553823587?mt=12\">iFax - Send &amp; Receive Faxes</a> [OS X, Category: Business, Free]</strong> The best-selling fax app for iOS is now on the Mac.</p><p style=\"padding:5px;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/04/new-and-notable-apps-for-ios-and-os-x-april-4-edition/\">New and notable apps for iOS and OS X - April 4 edition</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Thu, 04 Apr 2013 11:00:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear:both;\"></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=http://itunes.apple.com/>Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/04/new-and-notable-apps-for-ios-and-os-x-april-4-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://w