rgin:0 0 10px 0\"><img alt=\" \" border=\"0\" height=\"282\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com//media/2013/04/injusticegodsamongus.jpg\" width=\"450\" /></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 10px;\">
Injustice: Gods Among Us is a game that's been coming to consoles for a while now -- it's a fighting game, made by the same team behind Mortal Kombat, that features DC Universe superheroes battling it out against each other. The team has <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/injustice-gods-among-us/id575658129?mt=8\">released an iOS version of the game</a>, and while it's not exactly the same as the console titles, as you can see above, it looks pretty darn good anyway. This version is being made by the same division of NetherRealm that made <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2011/12/22/daily-iphone-app-batman-arkham-city-lockdown/\">Batman: Arkham City Lockdown</a> for Apple's devices, and just like that \"port,\" this game goes above and beyond the call of just creating a mobile-sized version of its console brothers.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 10px;\">
For one thing, the iOS version of Injustice will have three-on-three battles. You can see the interface for choosing a team and fighting <a href=\"http://www.ign.com/videos/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-ios-overview\">in this IGN video</a> -- you'll pick three heroes to fight with, and then attack back and forth by swiping various gestures across the screen. The graphics aren't exactly as cool as the console versions, but it looks like some of the same models are in use, and each hero comes with three levels of super moves, and can even be leveled up for higher hitpoints and damage.</p><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 10px;\">
The port looks very impressive indeed. I don't know if it'll be quite as good as the console game is looking, but it's clear NetherRealm isn't skimping on the quality when making an iOS version, and that's great to see. If you want to check the game out, you can <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/injustice-gods-among-us/id575658129?mt=8\">download it for free right now</a>.</p><p style=\"padding:5px;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/\">Injustice: Gods Among Us gets an original iOS version</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Wed, 03 Apr 2013 20:30:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear:both;\"></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/injustice-gods-among-us/id575658129?mt=8>Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/forward/20529268/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments</a>" "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/" (20828 37192) new 37 nil nil ((title nil "Injustice: Gods Among Us gets an original iOS version") (link nil "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/") (guid ((isPermaLink . "true")) "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/") (comments nil "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-or