	The port looks very impressive indeed. I don't know if it'll be quite as good as the console game is looking, but it's clear NetherRealm isn't skimping on the quality when making an iOS version, and that's great to see. If you want to check the game out, you can <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/injustice-gods-among-us/id575658129?mt=8\">download it for free right now</a>.</p><p style=\"padding:5px;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/\">Injustice: Gods Among Us gets an original iOS version</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Wed, 03 Apr 2013 20:30:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear:both;\"></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/injustice-gods-among-us/id575658129?mt=8>Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/forward/20529268/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/injustice-gods-among-us-gets-an-original-ios-version/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments</a>") (category nil "console") (category nil "freemium") (category nil "injustice") (category nil "injustice gods among us") (category nil "InjusticeGodsAmongUs") (category nil "iOS") (category nil "iPhone") (category nil "port") (category nil "tablet") (dc:creator nil "Mike Schramm") (pubDate nil "Wed, 03 Apr 2013 20:30:00 EST"))) ("Rdio introduces social video streaming service Vdio" "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\" \" border=\"0\" height=\"229\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com//media/2013/04/vdioheader-1365023108.jpg\" width=\"456\" /></p><p>
Online music-streaming service <a href=\"https://rdio.com\">Rdio</a> has announced the launch of <a href=\"http://vdio.com\">Vdio</a>, a new video-streaming service. Vdio is a pay-per-view service, unlike its sister program's \"all you can eat\" subscription model. The service builds off Rdio's social focus with Sets, playlists for TV shows and movies that make it easy to share and discover new content to watch. Furthering the social theme of the service is the ability to check out what your friends are watching at a given moment and jump into the program with them.</p><p>
A service is only as strong as its content, but Vdio features most of the latest releases from the big screen to network television. Current titles range from movies such as <em>Zero Dark Thirty</em> to <em>The Hobbit</em> and <em>Skyfall</em>, while popular television programs such as <em>Breaking Bad</em>, <em>Homeland</em> and <em>Downton Abbey</em> make up the broadcast front. TV shows are available to stream the day after they air, and subscribing to a whole season provides a discounted price. The service doesn't have a deal worked out with HBO, meaning you'll have to look elsewhere to catch up on <em>Game of Thrones</em>.</p><p>
At the moment the service is only available to Rdio Unlimited subscribers in the US and UK. Current subscribers, or anyone who subscribes in the next 60 days, will receive a US$25 credit towards the service to try it out.</p><p>
Vdio is currently only available on the iPad or online. Other devices and platforms will be added in the future. Curiously, the iPad app does not allow users to rent or download content, but rather only allows for streaming things that have already been purchased.</p><p style=\"padding:5px;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/\">Rdio introduces social video streaming service Vdio</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Wed, 03 Apr 2013 20:00:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear:both;\"></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=http://blog.rdio.com/us/2013/04/introducing-vdio.html>Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/forward/20529146/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments</a>" "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/" (20828 35392) new 38 nil nil ((title nil "Rdio introduces social video streaming service Vdio") (link nil "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/") (guid ((isPermaLink . "true")) "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/") (comments nil "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/#comments") (description nil "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img alt=\" \" border=\"0\" height=\"229\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com//media/2013/04/vdioheader-1365023108.jpg\" width=\"456\" /></p><p>
	Online music-streaming service <a href=\"https://rdio.com\">Rdio</a> has announced the launch of <a href=\"http://vdio.com\">Vdio</a>, a new video-streaming service. Vdio is a pay-per-view service, unlike its sister program's \"all you can eat\" subscription model. The service builds off Rdio's social focus with Sets, playlists for TV shows and movies that make it easy to share and discover new content to watch. Furthering the social theme of the service is the ability to check out what your friends are watching at a given moment and jump into the program with them.</p><p>
	A service is only as strong as its content, but Vdio features most of the latest releases from the big screen to network television. Current titles range from movies such as <em>Zero Dark Thirty</em> to <em>The Hobbit</em> and <em>Skyfall</em>, while popular television programs such as <em>Breaking Bad</em>, <em>Homeland</em> and <em>Downton Abbey</em> make up the broadcast front. TV shows are available to stream the day after they air, and subscribing to a whole season provides a discounted price. The service doesn't have a deal worked out with HBO, meaning you'll have to look elsewhere to catch up on <em>Game of Thrones</em>.</p><p>
	At the moment the service is only available to Rdio Unlimited subscribers in the US and UK. Current subscribers, or anyone who subscribes in the next 60 days, will receive a US$25 credit towards the service to try it out.</p><p>
	Vdio is currently only available on the iPad or online. Other devices and platforms will be added in the future. Curiously, the iPad app does not allow users to rent or download content, but rather only allows for streaming things that have already been purchased.</p><p style=\"padding:5px;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/\">Rdio introduces social video streaming service Vdio</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Wed, 03 Apr 2013 20:00:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear:both;\"></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=http://blog.rdio.com/us/2013/04/introducing-vdio.html>Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/forward/20529146/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/rdio-introduces-social-video-streaming-service-vdio/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments</a>") (category nil "iPad") (category nil "rdio") (category nil "streaming") (category nil "vdio") (dc:creator nil "John-Michael Bond") (pubDate nil "Wed, 03 Apr 2013 20:00:00 EST"))) ("Daily iPhone App: bit Dungeon is a retro RPG done well" "<p style=\"text-align:center;padding:0;margin:0 0 10px 0\"><img alt=\" \" border=\"0\" height=\"341\" src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com//media/2013/04/bitdungeonretro.jpg\" width=\"450\" /></p><p><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/bit-dungeon/id583949163?mt=8\">bit Dungeon</a> arrived on the App Store a little while ago, and if you missed it then, you'd do well to try it out now. Quite a few games have used the old 8-bit, top-down RPGs as a rubric, but bit Dungeon is probably the best example I've seen of all of them. You simply go from room to room, Legend of Zelda-style, hacking away at enemies, getting better gear and surviving as long as you can.</p><p>
The controls are interesting -- rather than using virtual controls, you simply tap on the screen to move around, and then again to attack. This ends up working kind of like Diablo, actually, where you tap to move out of the way of certain incoming spells or monsters, and then tap back in for your own offense when the way is clear. The scheme works very well, and it allows you quite a bit of precision when you need it.</p><p>
The game can be very harsh, in that when you die, that's essentially the end of that character. But I found health potions to be readily available, and as long as you make some smart choices while leveling up (and make sure you dodge as much as you can while in combat), the game is actually very rewarding and enjoyable. The great music and graphics help a lot as well. bit Dungeon is a really terrific title that's been a bit overlooked on the App Store. It's <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/bit-dungeon/id583949163?mt=8\">available for US$0.99</a>, and you definitely shouldn't miss out.</p><p style=\"padding:5px;clear:both;\"><a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/daily-iphone-app-bit-dungeon-is-a-retro-rpg-done-well/\">Daily iPhone App: bit Dungeon is a retro RPG done well</a> originally appeared on <a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com\">TUAW - The Unofficial Apple Weblog</a> on Wed, 03 Apr 2013 19:30:00 EST.  Please see our <a href=\"http://www.weblogsinc.com/feed-terms/\">terms for use of feeds</a>.<br style=\"clear:both;\"></p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/bit-dungeon/id583949163?mt=8>Source</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/daily-iphone-app-bit-dungeon-is-a-retro-rpg-done-well/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">Permalink</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/forward/20529169/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">Email this</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/daily-iphone-app-bit-dungeon-is-a-retro-rpg-done-well/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">Comments</a>" "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/daily-iphone-app-bit-dungeon-is-a-retro-rpg-done-well/" (20828 33592) new 39 nil nil ((title nil "Daily iPhone App: bit Dungeon is a retro RPG done well") (link nil "http://www.tuaw.com/2013/04/03/daily-iphone-app-bit-dungeon-is-a-retro-rpg-